body.description: Create an elegant, zero-maintenance floral display with this home decor creative building set for adults. This beautifully arranged build and display set is the perfect touch for your home, coffee table, or kitchen decor. The LEGO Icons Tiny Plants (10329) building project features flowers based on arid, tropical and carnivorous species, each nestled in a buildable, terracotta-colored pot. Enjoy time out crafting each of the 9 plants before displaying them in your home or office. This set makes a great gift for plant and flower-lovers, and is the perfect project to enjoy with friends and family. Suitable for both new and advanced builders, it includes different models for easy, medium, and advanced levels of building complexity. The LEGO Builder app features a digital version of the building instructions included with this set. Discover a space for relaxation with buildable models from the LEGO Botanical Collection, part of the inspiring range of LEGO building sets designed specifically for adults.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Unique and really fun gift!
reviews.reviewText: Do you have a plant aficionado in your family or friends circle? Do you want to keep plants but do not have a green thumb, do you want to make your place more colorful and fun? Then this set is just for you!!! We purchased this set as a gift for someone in the family who loves plants, succulents and flowers. They have a whole room dedicated to them and this set is a perfect activity and visual to add to their space. It was well received and I am sure that like every other set of Lego I have built or seen that the directions were incredibly detailed and easy to follow.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Lego set!
reviews.reviewText: These are really cool. They are small, but they work well for tiny spaces. I have them on my bar at home on the back counter. They would look good displayed on a coffee table, shelf or window sill They add color and everyone notices them. The booklets are cool too. They give you the history of the plants, correct names and trade names. I like that everything Lego makes is consistent yet challenging and fun to build.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this collection
reviews.reviewText: I am absolutely delighted with the LEGO Icons Tiny Plants Creative Building Set! As an adult LEGO enthusiast and a flower-lover, this set is a perfect blend of my interests. The attention to detail in each plant is remarkable, bringing a charming and realistic touch to my home decor without the worry of watering. The building process was a joy, offering a relaxing and enjoyable experience that is often sought after in adult LEGO sets. It makes for a fantastic and unique gift, especially for those who appreciate a touch of greenery in their space. The versatility in displaying these tiny plants is another plus, as they fit beautifully in various settings. A definite five-star rating for its creativity, quality, and the sheer joy it brings!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So cute and a fun hobby!
reviews.reviewText: The perfect excuse to get a Lego set as an adult! I also have an orchid(built one for myself, another for a family member). I can’t get enough of this Lego collection! All the pieces were included(always has extras)and instructions were easily understood. I timed myself on my phone as I built this set. I started a new lap as I opened the next bag. If you need a rainy day project or you’re looking for a hobby, this is it!
My husband did Lego for years and my granddaughter would help him. Now she is doing these new sets Lego is putting out. This one with succulents is so cute and should be fun to work on.
